rComments: Such a sweet prof. Really liked her.

not sure why her rating is so bad. yes she just reads the slides but if you study them and learn them by heart you'll do well. I stopped showing up to class near the end of the semester and still got A+ on the final just with her ppts (they're very detailed). as for the material taught, it's based off of the book so she can't be blamed for that

This prof was just "ok". She reads the powerpoints, every aspect comes from a textbook with dated content (mother is primary parent, children of divorce have a lot of issues...). The class isn't terrible: one proctored exam, few case studies and a proctored final, I just wouldn't take it again...

Not only did professor Levesque have no clue what she was teaching, the content was extremely stereotypical and very exclusive ("the mother is the primary parent" was literally in our class notes). I thought I was going to enjoy this class but it was horrible. I did not learn a thing, and the information that we needed to retain was so problematic.

DO NOT take a class with prof levesque. She has no idea what she's talking about. Her class is SOLELY based on a textbook and did not know how to answer anyone's questions. We had 1 midterm, a case study and a final. We were treated like a second thought. I definitely would never take her class again and I hope you don't either.
